      <byline class="print_byline">By Jayson Blair</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Blair, Jayson</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gov George E Pataki signs bill ending state requirement that shareholders approve company's use of stock options in compensation plans (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Gov. George E. Pataki signed a bill on Friday ending the state requirement that shareholders approve a company's use of stock options in compensation plans.</p>
        <p>The law was sought by technology companies and is expected to make it easier for them to offer employees stock options.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Gov. George E. Pataki signed a bill on Friday ending the state requirement that shareholders approve a company's use of stock options in compensation plans.</p>
        <p>The law was sought by technology companies and is expected to make it easier for them to offer employees stock options.</p>
        <p>Instead of requiring shareholder approval, the law allows companies to set up options plans for employees based on ''the policies of all stock exchanges or automated quotation systems on which the corporation's shares are listed or authorized for trading.''</p>
        <p>Jayson Blair (NYT)</p>
      </block>
